cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the task of cleaning scanned text documents, which involves image processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves probabilistic generative models and inference algorithms, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the effectiveness and efficiency of the approach, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
